13|X>C|route-mass-transport|fyi:PROPOSAL Route Mass Transport maps each removed teacher expert to two retained experts by output reconstruction, then initializes student logits from aggregated teacher mass;fyi:why exact copies make pruning constrained transport rather than relearning;n:cost=100k hidden samples,expected=30-60% lower initial reconstruction gap and 20-40% fewer rec steps;fyi:risk mapping shifts as backbone adapts, refresh once
14|X>C|missing-expert-replay|fyi:PROPOSAL Missing Expert Replay freezes the exact shared backbone, runs it once, then evaluates only the full teacher router and omitted top routes on identical hidden states;fyi:periodic full-teacher anchors cover later drift;n:teacher-compute-cut=63%,paired-compute-cut=35%,tr-storage=near-zero;fyi:risk local targets cease being exact after backbone updates, use early rec only
15|X>C|ghost-residual|fyi:PROPOSAL Ghost Residual distills omitted experts aggregate correction into one rank-128 gated residual network per layer while retaining 32 literal experts;fyi:why correlated removed routes may share low-dimensional error;n:add-params=22M,compute=<1%,expected=20-40% pruning-gap recovery;fyi:risk correction may not be low-rank, reject unless held-out gain survives phase buckets
16|X>C|annealed-routing|fyi:PROPOSAL Annealed Routing uses global top1 at high noise, top2 mid-denoise, top6 for final correction, with phase-conditioned teacher-mass distillation;fyi:why early random states need less specialization while late decisions deserve capacity;n:average-active=2.5,active-compute-cut=9%,expected-wall-win=5-10%;fyi:risk high-noise routing may seed irreversible errors, gate quality by phase
